Courtesy #DStv403 #eNCA JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa has refuted what he claims are false allegations made by Advocate Malesela Teffo. The advocate claims the Presidency is behind his alleged intimidation and his subsequent decision to withdraw from the Senzo Meyiwa murder trial. READ: Legal expert: Teffo’s behaviour 'inexcusable' Teffo claims he has been harassed by the police, the court and the state. Meyiwa’s family lawyer Gerrie Nel says this withdrawal will certainly cause delays to the case. He says this is an injustice to the family who just wants to find closure and have the perpetrator brought to book. Watch the video above for more details. THE PRESIDENCY REFUTES ADV TEFFO’S BASELESS TIRADE
The Presidency has noted and strongly refutes the false claims made by Advocate Malesela Teffo that the Presidency is behind his alleged intimidation and subsequent decision to withdraw from the Senzo Meyiwa murder trial.